sentences.english: Fourth, carpe diem means don't waste time.
sentences.chinese: 第四，及時行樂意謂著不浪費時間。

sentences.english: The word “dentist”denotes a doctor whose work is the care of teeth.
sentences.chinese: “牙科醫生”一詞意謂其工作是醫治牙齒的醫生。

sentences.english: We need to reassess what it means to work at 100%.

sentences.english: Second, carpe diem means time is a precious gift.
sentences.chinese: 第二，及時行樂意謂著時間是一份很珍貴的禮物。

sentences.english: This meant that they could enjoy ice treats all year long.
sentences.chinese: 這意謂着他們一整年都可以享受冰品。

sentences.english: Their hunting means that the many other fish in ocean waters do not become too great.

sentences.english: What does that mean--we are the political animal.
sentences.chinese: 但，“我們都是政治動物“意謂着什麼。

sentences.english: As with many things, agreeing on something means some kind of commitment.

sentences.english: Finning , as it is called, means cutting the fins off a live shark.

sentences.english: That doesn't mean that the hard-working student and athlete has never told a lie.
